      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until browned and very crispy, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>\n<p>Once crispy, transfer the <strong>crispy pork</strong> to a plate and set aside</p>\n<p>Reserve the pan</p>",
