    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>tahini</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Sriracha hot chilli sauce</strong></span>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and<span class=\"text-highlight\"> </span><strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">Chinese rice</span> wine</strong> with 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [80ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> spicy sesame sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Bash the<strong> peanuts</strong> with a <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>rolling pin</strong></span> until roughly crushed (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p>",
